             sworn.</p>
               <p>I am one of the clerks at Messrs. Clark and Co. at Liverpool: On the 18th of October last, I received 810 l. in bank notes from Mr. Annesdale; I put down each note in his banking book; there were a 500 l. a 200 l. a 100 l. and a 10 l. I put them forwards to the clerk who copies he notes in the bill book.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17861213-113-person1055">
